articles.author: Joseph Ax
articles.description: The dizzying presidential contest between Republican Donald Trump and Democrat Kamala Harris hurtled toward an uncertain finish as millions of Americans headed to the polls to choose between two sharply different visions for the country.
articles.title: Voters head to polls as turbulent campaign concludes

articles.author: Jonathan Saul
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's rightist government celebrated on Wednesday after Republican Donald Trump claimed victory in the U.S. presidential election.
articles.title: Israel's rightist government celebrates as Trump claims victory

articles.author: Mubasher Bukhari
articles.description: Pakistan's province of Punjab set up a "smog war room" to tackle severe pollution, officials said, as poor air quality turned its capital of Lahore into the world's most polluted city and forced the closure of some educational institutions.
articles.title: Pakistan's Punjab sets up 'smog war room' to combat hazardous air, shuts schools

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanese rescuers scoured the rubble of a destroyed apartment building south of Beirut on Wednesday for bodies or any survivors of an Israeli strike that health authorities said killed at least 20 people the previous evening.
articles.title: Lebanese rescuers scour site of Israeli strike south of Beirut that killed 20

articles.author: Guy Faulconbridge, Andrew Osborn
articles.description: New opportunities to reset relations between Moscow and Washington have opened up, the influential head of Russia's sovereign wealth fund said on Wednesday after Donald Trump declared victory in the U.S. presidential election.
articles.title: Russia floats idea of 'reset' with United States after Trump declares victory

articles.author: Matt Spetalnick
articles.description: While campaigning to regain the U.S. presidency, Donald Trump said that he would be able to end Russia's war in Ukraine in 24 hours, warned that Israel would be "eradicated" if he lost the election and vowed sweeping new tariffs on Chinese imports.
articles.title: Trump's erratic foreign policy to meet 'a world on fire'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Voters approved most of the referendums expanding the right to abortion in U.S. states on Tuesday, while Florida, Nebraska and South Dakota rejected such measures, giving anti-abortion advocates their first victories since the U.S. Supreme Court ended the constitutional right to the procedure in 2022.
articles.title: Florida, two other states defy trend and vote down abortion rights

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Korea's presidential office said on Wednesday that it will build a "perfect" security partnership with a new U.S. administration.
articles.title: South Korea says to build perfect security partnership with new U.S. administration

articles.author: Sarah Marsh, Andreas Rinke
articles.description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz's coalition faces a make-or-break moment on Wednesday as leaders of the three parties convene to forge compromises between their differing visions on rescuing the economy from decline.
articles.title: Germany's awkward coalition faces make-or-break moment

articles.author: Andy Sullivan
articles.description: Republicans took a step toward winning control of the U.S. Senate with a victory in West Virginia on Tuesday, while neither party appeared to have an edge in the battle for the House of Representatives.
articles.title: Republicans pick up one seat in battle for US Senate; House control at stake as well
